        "q": "Do SoHo cast-iron buildings have water damage problems?",
        "a": "Frequently. Cast-iron construction from the 1860s-1890s predates modern weatherproofing and vapor barriers. Water intrusion through the building envelope is common, especially around window frames and at roof level. An inspector should check for active leaks, water staining, and mold growth behind exposed brick walls. In SoHo's high-rent market, landlords often paint over water damage rather than fix the underlying building envelope issues."
