        "a": "SoHo pricing runs slightly above Manhattan averages due to building access complexity and specialized techniques needed for cast-iron lofts. Simple items like nightstands cost $75-$100, while complex pieces like PAX wardrobes or platform beds run $150-$250. The main SoHo-specific cost factor is floor leveling and wall anchoring — assemblers often spend extra time shimming furniture and using specialized fasteners for century-old plaster walls."
